      "house_ger": {
        "id": "963d38b6-502d-48aa-8ec7-50fc6344ab69",
        "name": "CHEF’S KITCHEN-15% SUMMER DISCOUNT! Furnished,DW,WD,near Kaneohe Bay",
        "location": "Lilipuna Road",
        "mainpic": "4bd9b71e-63e4-4260-ac16-2dd062064a69",
        "msg": "QR Code Link to This Post *** We are currently offering a three-month Summer Special (15% discount rental price) for the Dolphin Apartment for July, and August 2026 of $2,250/mo. (September 1st – 27th = 2650 * 0.9 = $2385). The Dolphin is already off market under lease at full price starting September 29*** In September, its price will return to its normal at $2,650/mo. Wake to the sounds of birds. Try a THREE month (negotiable) stay in our beautiful one bedroom hideaway in Kaneohe! Close to Kāne’ohe Bay, Coconut Island, lots of birds, fresh air, sea breezes -- citrus and banana trees…perfect for kayakers, runners, bicyclists, and sailors, including a large private grotto with six person table in the shade of a large lychee tree. and raised bed garden areas for folks who like to grow organic vegetables. There’s plenty of room for you to store a kayak and bicycle on the property. Great morning run on the loop to the Bay… • $2,250/mo. for July, August (normal price is $2,650/mo.) (September 1st – 27th = 2650 * 0.9 = $2385) • For photos and details see: https://hawaiiwindward.wordpress.com Read the intro page, then click the Dolphin link. • Available from: July 4, 2026 (negotiable) If you are interested, please click REPLY and write us telling a little about yourself and when would be good to call. We will be happy to get in touch and answer any Dolphin apartment questions you might have. Wake up to the sound of birds, fresh air and great sea breezes. eat bananas, pitanga, papaya and pomelos fresh from the trees in the yard. . . walk to Kaneohe Bay. Tastefully-furnished designer one bedroom apartment with full chef's kitchen in Kaneohe, near Kaneohe Bay, ringed by Pali mountain range. Dedicated parking on property just steps from the entry. Nice QUIET neighborhood (no bars on windows or doors here!). Our hideaway on a private cul-de-sac on the tranquil Windward side of O`ahu is peaceful and quiet. Less than a 10 minute walk to the kayaking and sailing paradise of Kaneohe Bay, HIMB’s Moku O Loe lab, restaurants, shopping and a yacht club. Quiet, and perfect for students, post-docs, HIMB Moku O Loe is a short walk (1km, 6/10ths mile) from the front door. We are less than 10 minutes from freeways to town (H3, Likelike, Pali Hwy). You can walk to Kaneohe movie theatres, malls, private yacht club; home-style cooking and fine dining are nearby. Tastefully furnished, featuring an art collection including Kastner brothers' photography and Asian art. The apartment is fully furnished, with all appliances, kitchen gear, pots, pans, dishes, silverware, sheets, towels – basically, everything you need. You could literally show up with luggage and a toothbrush! This is a peaceful neighborhood so we are definitely seeking someone quiet. Best for serious/studious professional. Previous tenants have included grad students, post-docs, doctors, nurses, teachers, newly-weds, and military officers. Main house is occupied by busy professionals. Apartment is attached to the main house (completely separate entrance, very private.) We love to kayak, sail, bicycle, run and hike and are happy to show you some great trails, kayak access points, etc. This rarely available, fully-furnished designer 1 BR apartment features: * Two covered lanai, one enclosed with locking gate and hammock (storage for sports gear). * Tile floors throughout the apartment. * Upgraded large kitchen with full-size gas stove/oven, dishwasher, microwave oven, coffee maker, toaster. Comes fully furnished with pots, pans, dishes, flatware, glasses, etc. * Upgraded bathroom -- tub/with handshower, tile floors, lots of storage. * Large washer/dryer inside apartment; Living room with 55\" Smart TV, double bed futon. * Dedicated on-property parking. * Access to raised beds for organic gardening and six-person lychee tree dining platform. * Strictly no pets. * Strict no smoking / vaping policy. No exceptions. * Credit report & background check required. $2,250/mo. (normal price $2650/mo.) * $45 credit/background check fee with application, refundable at lease signing.",
