        "msg": "QR Code Link to This Post the center of Hawaii Kai is a 32 Unit 1-Bedroom and 2-Bedroom Affordable Housing Project. This project is located approximately 1 1/2 blocks from the Safeway and McDonald's Mall at 6950 Hawaii Kai Drive. All applicants must be 62 years of age or older and have a combined gross income of under $53,900 for 1-Senior & $61,600 for 2-Seniors at 50% of Area Medium Income (AMI). A 1-Bedroom 1-Bath Unit rents for $800 a month at 50% of AMI and is 524 Sq. Ft. & A 2-Bedroom 1-Bath Unit rents for $1300 a month at 50% of AMI. So the maximum rent a tenant or tenants can pay for a 1-Bedroom 1-Bath Unit is $1,443. Rent does include electricity for everything except A/C. Rent also includes sewer and water. There is no A/C in the units and the only allowed A/C are the portable units and you have to pay the excess electricity to run your own A/C.",
